  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Kubernetes only use etcd's lease API for creating event objects. Event objects' lease lasts for 1 hour and doesn't need good precision. However, Kubernetes creates one lease on each create operation, and potentially many leases on GuaranteedUpdate(). This is unnecessary. It also causes big load (observed 100K+ leases in kubemark) in large scale.\r\n\r\nAn optimization is to have a lease that last for 1 minute and all events API to reuse that lease within the same minute instead of creating new lease on every operation.",
